rt, from 1.24 million in 2002 to peak at 2.46 million in 2011. Because of the financial crisis in Spain, those numbers decreased to 2.1 million in 2014. Cargo has decreased significantly over the last ten years. The Spanish economic recovery in the mid-2010s and the rise of Santiago de Compostela as an international destination are again increasing passenger numbers, breaking the 2.50 million mark for the first time in 2016.<ref name=\"annual statistics\">{{cite web |title=Annual Statistics |url=http://www.aena-aeropuertos.es/csee/Satellite?Language=ES_ES&c=Page&cid=1113582476721&pagename=Estadisticas%2FEstadisticas&periodoInforme=Anual |publisher=Aena Aeropuertos S.A. |accessdate=17 October 2013 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n===Traffic figures by year===\n<div class=\"floatright\">\n{| style=\"border:solid 1px #aaa;\" cellpadding=\"10\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|+'''Santiago de Compostela Airport Passenger Totals 2000-2019 (millions)'''\n|-\n| <timeline>\nImageSize = width:auto height:250 barincrement:29\nPlotArea = left:30 bottom:15 top:10 right:15\nAlignBars = justify\nPeriod = from:0 till:3\nTimeAxis = orientation:vertical\n\nColors =\n id:gray    value:gray(0.5)\n  id:line1    value:gray(0.9)\n  id:line2    value:gray(0.7)\n\nScaleMajor = start:0 increment:1 gridcolor:line2\nScaleMinor = start:0 increment:1 gridcolor:line1\n\nPlotData=\n color:blue width:20\n bar:2000 from:start till:1.332\n bar:2001 from:start till:1.281\n bar:2002 from:start till:1.240\n bar:2003 from:start till:1.381\n bar:2004 from:start till:1.580\n bar:2005 from:start till:1.843\n bar:2006 from:start till:1.994\n bar:2007 from:start till:2.050\n bar:2008 from:start till:1.917\n bar:2009 from:start till:1.944\n bar:2010 from:start till:2.172\n bar:2011 from:start till:2.464\n bar:2012 from:start till:2.194\n bar:2013 from:start till:2.073\n bar:2014 from:start till:2.084\n bar:2015 from:start till:2.296 \n bar:2016 from:start till:2.510\n bar:2017 from:start till:2.644\n bar:2018 from:start till: